+## Private Artifact Preflight Recovery
+
+When a proposal is rejected as a private or session artifact, inspect whether the rejection came from the file path, fixture fields, or task wording.
+
+Required recovery behavior:
+
+- Do not create private DevHub session files, auth state, cookies, traces, screenshots, raw browser storage, uploads, submissions, payments, certifications, cancellations, MFA, CAPTCHA, account-creation, password-recovery, or inspection-scheduling artifacts.
+- A redacted audit ledger fixture may be commit-safe only when it stores no private browser/session material and uses placeholder values.
+- Avoid filenames that contain `session` while recovering from private-artifact preflight failures unless the task is explicitly repairing the preflight classifier.
+- Prefer names such as `draft_audit_ledger.json` for redacted audit ledgers.
+- If preflight rejects a commit-safe redacted fixture solely because the task title says `draft-session`, add or update daemon preflight classification coverage before retrying the domain fixture.
+- Keep classifier repair separate from domain implementation; prove true private artifacts remain refused.
 
